  <section id="candleCare" class="active-page-section" style="display: none;">
    <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <h2>Candle <em>Care</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="policy-content" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--charcoal); font-family: 'Jost', sans-serif;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.2rem;">Follow these simple guidelines to ensure a clean, safe, and long-lasting burn for your Cozy Aura Candles.</p>
      
      <h3 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--gold-dark); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">1. Trim the Wick</h3>
      <p>Always trim the cotton wick to 1/4 inch (approx. 6mm) before every single light. This controls the flame size, prevents soot, and prevents the glass container from overheating.</p>
      
      <h3 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--gold-dark); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">2. The First Burn is Key</h3>
      <p>When lighting your candle for the first time, allow it to burn until the wax melts completely to the outer glass edges (usually 2–3 hours). This establishes a "burn memory" and prevents the candle from tunneling down the center on future burns.</p>
      
      <h3 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--gold-dark); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">3. Limit Burn Time</h3>
      <p>Do not burn your candle for more than 4 hours at a time. Extinguish the flame, let the wax cool completely, trim the wick, and relight if desired.</p>
      
      <h3 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--gold-dark); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">4. Safety First</h3>
      <p>Never leave a burning candle unattended. Always burn on a flat, heat-resistant surface away from drafts, ceiling fans, children, pets, and flammable objects.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

